obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (9670)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9670&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) This Act may be called the Commercial Courts`
  line `Act, 2015.]`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall be deemed to have come into force on the 23rd day of October, 2015.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 3 for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the fifth Schedule (w.e.f. 31- 10-2019).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (9671)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9671&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,---`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "Commercial Appellate Courts" means the Commercial Appellate Courts designated under`
  line `section 3A;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] "Commercial Appellate Division" means the Commercial Appellate Division in a High`
  line `Court constituted under sub-section (1) of section 5;`
  line
  line `(b) "Commercial Court" means the Commercial Court constituted under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "commercial dispute" means a dispute arising out of---`
  line
  line `(i) ordinary transactions of merchants, bankers, financiers and traders such as those relating to`
  line `mercantile documents, including enforcement and interpretation of such documents;`
  line
  line `(ii) export or import of merchandise or services;`
  line
  line `(iii) issues relating to admiralty and maritime law;`
  line
  line `(iv) transactions relating to aircraft, aircraft engines, aircraft equipment and helicopters,`
  line `including sales, leasing and financing of the same;`
  line
  line `(v) carriage of goods;`
  line
  line `(vi) construction and infrastructure contracts, including tenders;`
  line
  line `(vii) agreements relating to immovable property used exclusively in trade or commerce;`
  line
  line `(viii) franchising agreements;`
  line
  line `(ix) distribution and licensing agreements;`
  line
  line `(x) management and consultancy agreements;`
  line
  line `(xi) joint venture agreements;`
  line
  line `(xii) shareholders agreements;`
  line
  line `(xiii) subscription and investment agreements pertaining to the services industry including`
  line `outsourcing services and financial services;`
  line
  line `(xiv) mercantile agency and mercantile usage;`
  line
  line `(xv) partnership agreements;`
  line
  line `(xvi) technology development agreements;`
  line
  line `(xvii) intellectual property rights relating to registered and unregistered trademarks,`
  line `copyright, patent, design, domain names, geographical indications and semiconductor integrated`
  line circuits;
  line
  line `(xviii) agreements for sale of goods or provision of services;`
  line
  line `(xix) exploitation of oil and gas reserves or other natural resources including electromagnetic`
  line spectrum;
  line
  line `(xx) insurance and re-insurance;`
  line
  line `(xxi) contracts of agency relating to any of the above; and`
  line
  line `(xxii) such other commercial disputes as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--- A commercial dispute shall not cease to be a commercial dispute merely`
  line because---
  line
  line `(a) it also involves action for recovery of immovable property or for realisation of monies`
  line `out of immovable property given as security or involves any other relief pertaining to`
  line `immovable property;`
  line
  line `(b) one of the contracting parties is the State or any of its agencies or instrumentalities, or`
  line `a private body carrying out public functions;`
  line
  line `(d) "Commercial Division" means the Commercial Division in a High Court constituted under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `(e) "District Judge" shall have the same meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of article 236 of`
  line `the Constitution of India;`
  line
  line `(f) "document" means any matter expressed or described upon any substance by means of letters,`
  line `figures or marks, or electronic means, or by more than one of those means, intended to be used, or`
  line `which may be used, for the purpose of recording that matter;`
  line
  line `(g) "notification" means a notification published in the Official Gazette and the expression`
  line `"notify" with its cognate meanings and grammatical variations shall be construed accordingly;`
  line
  line `(h) "Schedule" means the Schedule appended to the Act; and`
  line
  line `(i) "Specified Value", in relation to a commercial dispute, shall mean the value of the`
  line `subject-matter in respect of a suit as determined in accordance with section 12 ^3[which shall not be`
  line `less than three lakh rupees] or such higher value, as may be notified by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The words and expressions used and not defined in this Act but defined in the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) and the Indian Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), shall have the same`
  line `meanings respectively assigned to them in that Code and the Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 4, (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) renumbered as clause (aa) by s. 4, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "which shall not be less than one crore rupees" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (9672)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Constitution of Commercial Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9672&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `CHAPTER II`
  line
  line `^1[COMMERCIAL COURTS, COMMERCIAL APPELLATE COURTS, COMMERCIAL DIVISIONS AND COMMERCIAL`
  line `APPELLATE DIVISIONS].`
  line
  line `Constitution of Commercial Courts.--- (1) The State Government, may after consultation with the`
  line `concerned High Court, by notification, constitute such number of Commercial Courts at District level, as`
  line `it may deem necessary for the purpose of exercising the jurisdiction and powers conferred on those`
  line `Courts under this Act:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that with respect to the High Courts having ordinary original civil jurisdiction, the State`
  line `Government may, after consultation with the concerned High Court, by notification, constitute`
  line `Commercial Courts at the District Judge level:`
  line
  line `Provided further that with respect to a territory over which the High Courts have ordinary original`
  line `civil jurisdiction, the State Government may, by notification, specify such pecuniary value which shall`
  line `not be less than three lakh rupees and not more than the pecuniary jurisdiction exercisable by the District`
  line `Courts, as it may consider necessary.]`
  line
  line `^3[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in this Act, the State Government may, after consultation`
  line `with the concerned High Court, by notification, specify such pecuniary value which shall not be less than`
  line `three lakh rupees or such higher value, for whole or part of the State, as it may consider necessary.]`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government shall, after consultation with the concerned High Court specify, by`
  line `notification, the local limits of the area to which the jurisdiction of a Commercial Court shall extend and`
  line `may, from time to time, increase, reduce or alter such limits.`
  line
  line `(3) The ^4[State Government may], with the concurrence of the Chief Justice of the High Court appoint`
  line `one or more persons having experience in dealing with commercial disputes to be the Judge or Judges, of`
  line `a ^5[Commercial Court either at the level of District Judge or a court below the level of a District Judge].`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 5, for "CONSTITUTION OF COMMERCIAL COURTS, COMMERCIAL DIVISIONS AND`
  line `COMMERCIAL APPELLATE DIVISIONS" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for the proviso (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 6, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "State Government shall" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "Commercial Court, from amongst the cadre of Higher Judicial Service in the State"`
  line `(w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_3_a:
  sectionId (48974)
  sectionNo 3A
  orderNo 4
  title `Designation of Commercial Appellate Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 7 (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=48974&sectionno=3A&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_3_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[3A. Designation of Commercial Appellate Courts.--- Except the territories over which the High`
  line `Courts have ordinary original civil jurisdiction, the State Government may, after consultation with the`
  line `concerned High Court, by notification, designate such number of Commercial Appellate Courts at District`
  line `Judge level, as it may deem necessary, for the purposes of exercising the jurisdiction and powers`
  line `conferred on those Courts under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (9673)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Constitution of Commercial Division of High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 8, for "ordinary civil jurisdiction" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9673&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) In all High Courts, having ^1[ordinary`
  line `original civil jurisdiction], the Chief Justice of the High Court may, by order, constitute Commercial`
  line `Division having one or more Benches consisting of a single Judge for the purpose of exercising the`
  line `jurisdiction and powers conferred on it under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Justice of the High Court shall nominate such Judges of the High Court who have`
  line `experience in dealing with commercial disputes to be Judges of the Commercial Division.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (9674)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 6
  title `Constitution of Commercial Appellate Division.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9674&sectionno=5&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) After issuing notification under subsection`
  line `(1) of section 3 or order under sub-section (1) of section 4, the Chief Justice of the concerned`
  line `High Court shall, by order, constitute Commercial Appellate Division having one or more Division`
  line `Benches for the purpose of exercising the jurisdiction and powers conferred on it by the Act.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chief Justice of the High Court shall nominate such Judges of the High Court who have`
  line `experience in dealing with commercial disputes to be Judges of the Commercial Appellate Division.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (9675)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Jurisdiction of Commercial Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9675&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Commercial Court shall have jurisdiction to try all suits`
  line `and applications relating to a commercial dispute of a Specified Value arising out of the entire territory of`
  line `the State over which it has been vested territorial jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, a commercial dispute shall be considered to arise out`
  line `of the entire territory of the State over which a Commercial Court has been vested jurisdiction, if the suit`
  line `or application relating to such commercial dispute has been instituted as per the provisions of sections 16`
  line `to 20 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (9676)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Jurisdiction of Commercial Divisions of High Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9676&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `All suits and applications relating to`
  line `commercial disputes of a Specified Value filed in a High Court having ordinary original civil jurisdiction`
  line `shall be heard and disposed of by the Commercial Division of that High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that all suits and applications relating to commercial disputes, stipulated by an Act to lie in a`
  line `court not inferior to a District Court, and filed or pending on the original side of the High Court, shall be`
  line `heard and disposed of by the Commercial Division of the High Court:`
  line
  line `Provided further that all suits and applications transferred to the High Court by virtue of sub-section`
  line `(4) of section 22 of the Designs Act, 2000 (16 of 2000) or section 104 of the Patents Act, 1970 (39 of`
  line `1970) shall be heard and disposed of by the Commercial Division of the High Court in all the areas over`
  line `which the High Court exercises ordinary original civil jurisdiction.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (9677)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Bar against revision application or petition against an interlocutory order.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9677&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, no civil revision application or petition`
  line `shall be entertained against any interlocutory order of a Commercial Court, including an order on the`
  line `issue of jurisdiction, and any such challenge, subject to the provisions of section 13, shall be raised only`
  line `in an appeal against the decree of the Commercial Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (9678)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Transfer of suit if counterclaim in a commercial dispute is of Specified Value.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9678&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `[Transfer of suit if counterclaim in a commercial dispute is of Specified Value].-- Omitted by the`
  line `Commercial Courts, Commercial Division and Commercial Appellate Division of High Courts`
  line `(Amendment) Act, 2018 (28 of 2018), s. 9 (w.e.f. 3-5-2018)`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (9679)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Jurisdiction in respect of arbitration matters.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9679&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Where the subject-matter of an arbitration is a`
  line `commercial dispute of a Specified Value and--`
  line
  line `(1) If such arbitration is an international commercial arbitration, all applications or appeals arising out`
  line `of such arbitration under the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996) that`
  line `have been filed in a High Court, shall be heard and disposed of by the Commercial Division where such`
  line `Commercial Division has been constituted in such High Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If such arbitration is other than an international commercial arbitration, all applications or appeals`
  line `arising out of such arbitration under the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of`
  line `1996) that have been filed on the original side of the High Court, shall be heard and disposed of by the`
  line `Commercial Division where such Commercial Division has been constituted in such High Court.`
  line
  line `(3) If such arbitration is other than an international commercial arbitration, all applications or appeals`
  line `arising out of such arbitration under the provisions of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of`
  line `1996) that would ordinarily lie before any principal civil court of original jurisdiction in a district (not`
  line `being a High Court) shall be filed in, and heard and disposed of by the Commercial Court exercising`
  line `territorial jurisdiction over such arbitration where such Commercial Court has been constituted.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (9680)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Bar of jurisdiction of Commercial Courts and Commercial Divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9680&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line Notwithstanding
  line `anything contained in this Act, a Commercial Court or a Commercial Division shall not entertain or`
  line `decide any suit, application or proceedings relating to any commercial dispute in respect of which the`
  line `jurisdiction of the civil court is either expressly or impliedly barred under any other law for the time being`
  line `in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (9681)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Determination of Specified Value.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9681&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Specified Value of the subject-matter of the`
  line `commercial dispute in a suit, appeal or application shall be determined in the following manner:---`
  line
  line `(a) where the relief sought in a suit or application is for recovery of money, the money sought to`
  line `be recovered in the suit or application inclusive of interest, if any, computed up to the date of filing of`
  line `the suit or application, as the case may be, shall be taken into account for determining such Specified`
  line Value;
  line
  line `(b) where the relief sought in a suit, appeal or application relates to movable property or to a right`
  line `therein, the market value of the movable property as on the date of filing of the suit, appeal or`
  line `application, as the case may be, shall be taken into account for determining such Specified Value;`
  line
  line `(c) where the relief sought in a suit, appeal or application relates to immovable property or to a`
  line `right therein, the market value of the immovable property, as on the date of filing of the suit, appeal`
  line `or application, as the case may be, shall be taken into account for determining Specified Value; ^1[and]`
  line
  line `(d) where the relief sought in a suit, appeal or application relates to any other intangible right, the`
  line `market value of the said rights as estimated by the plaintiff shall be taken into account for`
  line `determining Specified Value; ^2***`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) The aggregate value of the claim and counterclaim, if any as set out in the statement of claim and`
  line `the counterclaim, if any, in an arbitration of a commercial dispute shall be the basis for determining`
  line `whether such arbitration is subject to the jurisdiction of a Commercial Division, Commercial Appellate`
  line `Division or Commercial Court, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(3) No appeal or civil revision application under section 115 of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908), as the case may be, shall lie from an order of a Commercial Division or Commercial Court`
  line `finding that it has jurisdiction to hear a commercial dispute under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 10 (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by s. 10, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (e) omitted by s. 10, ibid., (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (48975)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 14
  title `Pre-Institution Mediation and Settlement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 11 (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=48975&sectionno=12A&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[CHAPTER IIIA`
  line
  line `PRE-INSTITUTION MEDIATION AND SETTLEMENT`
  line
  line `12A. Pre-Institution Mediation and Settlement.--- (1) A suit, which does not contemplate any urgent`
  line `interim relief under this Act, shall not be instituted unless the plaintiff exhausts the remedy of preinstitution mediation in accordance with such manner and procedure as may be prescribed by rules made`
  line `by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) The Central Government may, by notification, authorise the Authorities constituted under the`
  line `Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987), for the purposes of pre-institution mediation.`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Legal Services Authorities Act, 1987 (39 of 1987), the`
  line `Authority authorised by the Central Government under sub-section (2) shall complete the process of`
  line `mediation within a period of three months from the date of application made by the plaintiff under`
  line `sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided that the period of mediation may be extended for a further period of two months with the`
  line `consent of the parties:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, the period during which the parties remained occupied with the pre-institution`
  line `mediation, such period shall not be computed for the purpose of limitation under the Limitation Act, 1963`
  line `(36 of 1963).`
  line
  line `(4) If the parties to the commercial dispute arrive at a settlement, the same shall be reduced into`
  line `writing and shall be signed by the parties to the dispute and the mediator.`
  line
  line `(5) The settlement arrived at under this section shall have the same status and effect as if it is an`
  line `arbitral award on agreed terms under sub-section (4) of section 30 of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act,`
  line `1996 (26 of 1996).]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (9682)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 15
  title `Appeals from decrees of Commercial Courts and Commercial Divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 12, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9682&sectionno=13&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1[Any person`
  line `aggrieved by the judgment or order of a Commercial Court below the level of a District Judge may appeal`
  line `to the Commercial Appellate Court within a period of sixty days from the date of judgment or order.`
  line
  line `(1A) Any person aggrieved by the judgment or order of a Commercial Court at the level of District`
  line `Judge exercising original civil jurisdiction or, as the case may be, Commercial Division of a High Court`
  line `may appeal to the Commercial Appellate Division of that High Court within a period of sixty days from`
  line `the date of the judgment or order:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appeal shall lie from such orders passed by a Commercial Division or a Commercial`
  line `Court that are specifically enumerated under Order XLIII of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) as amended by this Act and section 37 of the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996`
  line `(26 of 1996).]`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force or Letters Patent`
  line `of a High Court, no appeal shall lie from any order or decree of a Commercial Division or Commercial`
  line `Court otherwise than in accordance with the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (9683)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 16
  title `Expeditious disposal of appeals.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 13 for "Commercial Appellate Division" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9683&sectionno=14&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `The ^1[Commercial Appellate Court and the Commercial`
  line `Appellate Division] shall endeavour to dispose of appeals filed before it within a period of six months`
  line `from the date of filing of such appeal.`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (9684)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 17
  title `Transfer of pending cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 14, for "with Order XIV-A" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9684&sectionno=15&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `(1) All suits and applications, including applications under the`
  line `Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996 (26 of 1996), relating to a commercial dispute of a Specified`
  line `Value pending in a High Court where a Commercial Division has been constituted, shall be transferred to`
  line `the Commercial Division.`
  line
  line `(2) All suits and applications, including applications under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act, 1996`
  line `(26 of 1996), relating to a commercial dispute of a Specified Value pending in any civil court in any`
  line `district or area in respect of which a Commercial Court has been constituted, shall be transferred to such`
  line `Commercial Court:`
  line
  line `Provided that no suit or application where the final judgment has been reserved by the Court prior to`
  line `the constitution of the Commercial Division or the Commercial Court shall be transferred either under`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(3) Where any suit or application, including an application under the Arbitration and Conciliation`
  line `Act, 1996 (26 of 1996), relating to a commercial dispute of Specified Value shall stand transferred to the`
  line `Commercial Division or Commercial Court under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), the provisions of this`
  line `Act shall apply to those procedures that were not complete at the time of transfer.`
  line
  line `(4) The Commercial Division or Commercial Court, as the case may be, may hold case management`
  line `hearings in respect of such transferred suit or application in order to prescribe new timelines or issue such`
  line `further directions as may be necessary for a speedy and efficacious disposal of such suit or application in`
  line `accordance ^1[with Order XV-A] of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908):`
  line
  line `Provided that the proviso to sub-rule (1) of Rule 1 of Order V of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908`
  line `(5 of 1908) shall not apply to such transferred suit or application and the court may, in its discretion,`
  line `prescribe a new time period within which the written statement shall be filed.`
  line
  line `(5) In the event that such suit or application is not transferred in the manner specified in`
  line `sub-section (1), sub-section (2) or sub-section (3), the Commercial Appellate Division of the High Court`
  line `may, on the application of any of the parties to the suit, withdraw such suit or application from the court`
  line `before which it is pending and transfer the same for trial or disposal to the Commercial Division or`
  line `Commercial Court, as the case may be, having territorial jurisdiction over such suit, and such order of`
  line `transfer shall be final and binding.`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (9685)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 18
  title `Amendments to the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 in its application to commercial disputes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9685&sectionno=16&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908) shall, in their application`
  line `to any suit in respect of a commercial dispute of a Specified Value, stand amended in the manner as`
  line `specified in the Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commercial Division and Commercial Court shall follow the provisions of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), as amended by this Act, in the trial of a suit in respect of a commercial`
  line `dispute of a Specified Value.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any provision of any Rule of the jurisdictional High Court or any amendment to the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), by the State Government is in conflict with the provisions of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), as amended by this Act, the provisions of the Code of Civil`
  line `Procedure as amended by this Act shall prevail.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (9686)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 19
  title `Collection and disclosure of data by Commercial Courts, Commercial Divisions and Commercial Appellate Divisions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 15, for "Commercial Courts" and "Commercial Court" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9686&sectionno=17&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `17. Collection and disclosure of data by ^1[Commercial Courts, Commercial Appellate Courts],`
  line `Commercial Divisions and Commercial Appellate Divisions.--The statistical data regarding the`
  line `number of suits, applications, appeals or writ petitions filed before the ^1[Commercial Courts, Commercial`
  line `Appellate Courts], Commercial Division, or Commercial Appellate Division, as the case may be, the`
  line `pendency of such cases, the status of each case, and the number of cases disposed of, shall be maintained`
  line `and updated every month by each ^1[Commercial Courts, Commercial Appellate Courts], Commercial`
  line `Division, Commercial Appellate Division and shall be published on the website of the relevant High`
  line Court.
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (9687)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power of High Court to issue directions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9687&sectionno=18&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The High Court may, by notification, issue practice`
  line `directions to supplement the provisions of Chapter II of this Act or the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5`
  line `of 1908) insofar as such provisions apply to the hearing of commercial disputes of a Specified Value.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (9688)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Infrastructure facilities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9688&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The State Government shall provide necessary infrastructure to`
  line `facilitate the working of a Commercial Court or a Commercial Division of a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (9689)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title `Training and continuous education.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 16 for "Commercial Court" (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9689&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may, in consultation with the`
  line `High Court, establish necessary facilities providing for training of Judges who may be appointed to the ^1[Commercial Courts, Commercial Appellate Courts], Commercial Division or the Commercial Appellate`
  line `Division in a High Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (9690)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Act to have overriding effect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9690&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise provided, the provisions of this Act shall have`
  line `effect, notwithstanding anything inconsistent therewith contained in any other law for the time being in`
  line `force or in any instrument having effect by virtue of any law for the time being in force other than this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21_a:
  sectionId (48976)
  sectionNo 21A
  orderNo 24
  title `Power of Central Government to make rules`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 28 of 2018, s. 17 (w.e.f. 3-5-2018).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=48976&sectionno=21A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_21_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[21A. Power of Central Government to make rules.--- (1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification, make rules for carrying out the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for or any of the following matters, namely:---`
  line
  line `(a) the manner and procedure of pre-institution mediation under sub-section (1) of section 12A;`
  line
  line `(b) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed or in respect of which`
  line `provision is to be made by rules made by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session, or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule, or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (9691)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9691&sectionno=22&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of`
  line `this Act, the Central Government may, by order published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions,`
  line `not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient for`
  line `removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made under this section after the expiry of a period of two years`
  line `from the date of commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be, after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (9692)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 26
  title `Repeal and savings.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347&sectionId=9692&sectionno=23&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_46_00008_201604_1517807328347
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commercial Courts, Commercial Division and Commercial`
  line `Appellate Division of High Courts Ordinance, 2015 (Ord. 8 of 2015) is hereby repealed.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action taken under the said Ordinance, shall be`
  line `deemed to have been done or taken under the corresponding provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
